comments.body:
Nice idea! I think that would work - I could do a full signet sync with it.

I'm still a bit undecided on general grounds, i.e. if it's okay to add more logic to accommodate a test-only mode that doesn't make sense for anything else but easier testing of pruning in the functional and unit tests. One could also argue that if no one but a developer would ever have a reason to use it, it'd be ok to just tell them more clearly not to create large blocks alongside using this option and abort otherwise?

@MarcoFalke : Do you have an opinion on this, or do you remember past discussions about test-only bitcoind options like this one?

